FBIS3-55230 "drsov005_g_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Kebich Says Russia Should Join NATO Before East Europe LD0601174094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1430 GMT 6 Jan 94 LD0601174094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Russia should become a member of NATO before the states of Eastern Europe and Lithuania join this organization. This was stated by Belarusian Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich in an interview for a RIA correspondent. He said that such a step will help to avoid military-political polarization in Europe. Kebich believes that, once Russia has joined NATO, Belarus may also become a member of that bloc.
